The Independent Corrupt Practices and Other Related Offences Commission (ICPC) says it  arrested nine persons for vote buying in Osun, Ondo, Borno, Akwa Ibom and Sokoto States during yesterday’s  Presidential and National Assembly Elections. According to the ICPC spokesperson, Mrs. Azuka Ogugua, four of the suspects  were arrested by the Osun State Office of the ICPC, while two persons were arrested by the Sokoto State Office. One person each was arrested by the Ondo, Akwa Ibom and Borno Offices of the anti-graft agency.